      "id": "PopularPost365628",
      "post_content": "This isn't 2.3 tier quality. This is a defender who's always on curve, then an attacker when you want it to be. A 2/2 on T2, a 3/3 on T3, a 4/4 on T4... and the moment you feel that you don't need your 5/5 or 6/6 to improve, it can become a strong offensive presence. And if your opponent killspells it, well, that's a kill spell that they've spent on something as low-investment as a 1/1 for ![1](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=1&type=symbol). It's win-win!",
